{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line 2 baking trays with baking paper."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place butter, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl then cream <nobr>2 min\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."," <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add flour and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Tip out onto a lightly-floured surface, bring together into a ball then wrap in cling film and chill in fridge for 30 minutes.","On a lightly-floured surface, roll out chilled dough to 5 mm thick then cut out hearts using a heart-shaped cookie cutter. Re-roll any trimmings and cut out more hearts until all dough is used.","Place on prepared trays and chill in fridge for 3 hours. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl. Towards the end of chilling time, preheat oven to 180째C.","Bake for 10-15 minutes (180째C) until pale golden. Leave to cool on trays for 5 minutes then carefully transfer to wire racks to cool completely (approx. 30 minutes).","Once shortbread hearts have cooled, place chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>8 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Remove 50 g (scales will show - 50 g), transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Add oil and melt <nobr>4 min\/50째C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add reserved grated chocolate, mix <nobr>3 min\/speed 2<\/nobr> then melt <nobr>40 sec\/37째C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to a small bowl (see tip).","Dip cooled shortbread hearts in melted chocolate so that half is coated, then place on 2 wire racks to set completely before serving or store in an airtight container (see tip)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["110 g unsalted butter, diced","100 g caster sugar","2 tsp vanilla extract","170 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","200 g dark chocolate, small pieces or callets","1 tsp coconut oil"]}],"id":"r355289","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-9F1ClDi82_w\/XZWrzH0rezI\/AAAAAAAAfs4\/RM3ponalHJ8xzKTXWxqVBC5AejEKLIFxwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_v_eI4P-4gJGT2Y5y.png","title":"Chocolate Dipped Shortbread Hearts","publishedAt":"2018-08-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"11 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"17 g","calories":"773 kJ \/ 185 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking trays, baking paper, rolling pin, wire racks, cling film, heart-shaped cookie cutter, airtight container, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["The smaller the bowl, the easier it will be to dip exactly half of the heart into the bowl.","The coconut oil makes it easier to work with the melted chocolate. If the chocolate on the biscuits is not set after <nobr>1 hour,<\/nobr> place biscuits in fridge for <nobr>10 minutes<\/nobr> to set fully before serving or store in an airtight container."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","5h","16 pieces"]}